#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:1
msgid "Pyodide Python compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:3
msgid "Python Standard library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:5
msgid ""
"Most of the Python standard library is functional, except for the modules "
"listed in the sections below. A large part of the CPython test suite passes "
"except for tests skipped in [`src/tests/python_tests.yaml`](https://github."
"com/pyodide/pyodide/blob/main/src/tests/python_tests.yaml) or via [patches]"
"(https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide/tree/main/cpython/patches)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:11
msgid "Optional modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:13
msgid ""
"The following stdlib modules are unvendored by default, in order to reduce "
"initial download size of Python distribution. You can load all unvendored "
"stdlib modules when initializing Pyodide with, `loadPyodide({ fullStdLib : "
"true })`. However this has a significant impact on the download size. "
"Instead, it is better to load individual modules as needed using {js:func}"
"`pyodide.loadPackage` or {py:func}`micropip.install`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:21
msgid "ssl"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:22
msgid "lzma"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:23
msgid "sqlite3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:24
msgid ""
"test: it is an exception to the above, since it is not loaded even if "
"`fullStdLib` is set to true."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:26
msgid "Modules with limited functionality"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:28
msgid ""
"hashlib: Hash algorithms that are depending on OpenSSL are not available by "
"default. See Python [hashlib documentation](https://docs.python.org/3/"
"library/hashlib.html) for list of algorithms that are dependent on OpenSSL. "
"If you need those algorithms, you need to call `pyodide."
"loadPackage('hashlib')` or `micropip.install('hashlib')` **before** "
"importing hashlib."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:34
msgid ""
"decimal: The decimal module has C (\\_decimal) and Python (\\_pydecimal) "
"implementations with the same functionality. The Python implementation is "
"not available by default. If you need a Python implementation of decimal, "
"you need to call `pyodide.loadPackage('pydecimal')` or `micropip."
"install('pydecimal')`, then explicitly import `_pydecimal`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:40
msgid ""
"pydoc: Help messages for Python builtins are not available by default in "
"order to reduce the initial download size. You need to call `pyodide."
"loadPackage('pydoc_data')` or `micropip.install('pydoc_data')` to enable "
"them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:45
msgid ""
"webbrowser: The original webbrowser module is not available. Instead, "
"Pyodide includes some method stubs based on browser APIs: `webbrowser."
"open()`, `webbrowser.open_new()`, `webbrowser.open_new_tab()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:49
msgid ""
"zoneinfo: The zoneinfo package will only work if you install the timezone "
"data using the tzdata package (i.e. by calling `pyodide."
"loadPackage(\"tzdata\")`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:52
msgid "Synchronous HTTP requests support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:54
msgid ""
"Packages for `urllib3` and `requests` are included in pyodide. In browser, "
"these function _roughly_ the same as on other operating systems with some "
"limitations. In node.js, they are currently untested, they will require at "
"least a polyfill for synchronous XMLHttpRequest, and WebWorker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:59
msgid ""
"The first limitation is that streaming download of files only works in very "
"specific circumstances, which are that pyodide has to be running in a web-"
"worker, and it has to be on a cross-origin isolated website. If either of "
"these conditions are not met, it will do a non-streaming request, i.e. "
"download the full request body before it returns from the initial request "
"call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/wasm-constraints.md:66
msgid ""
"Secondly, all network calls are done via the browser. This means you are "
"subject to the same limitations as any JavaScript network call. This means "
"you have very little or no control over certificates, timeouts, proxies and "
"other network related settings. You also are constrained by browser policies "
"relating to cross-origin requests, sometimes things will be blocked by CORS "
"policies if the server doesn't serve them with the correct headers."
msgstr ""

